001package io.cyborgcode.roa.framework.data;
002
003import java.util.Map;
004
005/**
006 * Defines a contract for providing static test data.
007 *
008 * <p>Implementing classes must define a method that returns a predefined
009 * set of key-value pairs to be used as test data during execution.
010 *
011 * <p>This interface is primarily used with annotations that specify static
012 * data providers, allowing the framework to dynamically load and inject
013 * test data before test execution.
014 *
015 * @author Cyborg Code Syndicate ğŸ’ğŸ‘¨ğŸ’»
016 */
017public interface StaticDataProvider {
018
019   /**
020    * Provides a set of predefined static test data.
021    *
022    * <p>The returned map contains key-value pairs representing test data
023    * that can be accessed during test execution.
024    *
025    * @return A map containing static test data.
026    */
027   Map<String, Object> staticTestData();
028
029}
